HEADWORD: Enhearten
<hw>En*heart"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To give heart
to; to fill with courage; to embolden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The enemy exults and is <qex>enheartened</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enhedge</ent>⟦br⟧
